2026-06-24 06:04:34,841 DEBUG msg #9: UserMessage tool_result(toolu_0112AKWmyRS7Urwyi6L6SvkV): 1	# FIFA World Cup 2026 Knockout Prediction
2	
3	Monte Carlo simulation of FIFA World Cup 2026 knockout outcomes using machine learning classifiers and statistical feature generation.
4	
5	## Overview
6	
7	This project predicts the FIFA World Cup 2026 knockout stage through a multi-stage pipeline:
8	
9	1. **Data acquisition** — downloads historical international and club match statistics from the [football-data.org](https://www.football-data.org/) REST API v4 via a rate-limited client with circuit-breaker retry logic
10	2. **Training** — fits three ML classifiers (SVM, Random Forest, Gaussian Naive Bayes) on historical match data (2006 onward) to predict the home/favoured team winning a single match
11	3. **Distribution fitting** — fits scipy statistical distributions to each national team's recent per-match performance (goals, shots, shots on target, possession, pass accuracy)
12	4. **Monte Carlo simulation** — samples synthetic match features from the fitted distributions, predicts each tie's outcome with the trained classifier, and runs thousands of full knockout brackets (Round of 32 → Round of 16 → Quarter-finals → Semi-finals → Final) to produce per-team advancement probabilities at every round
13	5. **Visualization** — renders a bracket PNG and round-probability charts
14	
15	Unlike the NBA original this project is derived from, World Cup knockout ties are decided by a **single match** — extra time and penalties collapse into one win/loss outcome — so there is no best-of-N series to configure anywhere in the pipeline.
16	
17	## Installation
18	
19	Requires Python 3.11+.
20	
21	```bash
22	git clone https://github.com/SilvioBaratto/worldcup-2026-prediction.git
23	cd worldcup-2026-prediction
24	pip install -e .
25	```
26	
27	For development (adds pytest, pytest-cov, ruff, mypy):
28	
29	```bash
30	pip install -e ".[dev]"
31	```
32	
33	Without editable install:
34	
35	```bash
36	pip install -r requirements.txt
37	```
38	
39	### API key
40	
41	The football-data.org client reads its key from the `FOOTBALL_DATA_API_KEY` environment variable and sends it as the `X-Auth-Token` header. The client works **unauthenticated** as well, but is then subject to the free-tier rate limit of 10 requests/minute (the default 6 s spacing between calls is tuned for exactly this).
42	
43	```bash
44	export FOOTBALL_DATA_API_KEY="your-token-here"
45	```
46	
47	## Quick Start
48	
49	```bash
50	# Run the full pipeline: clean → train → fit → simulate → visualize
51	worldcup-playoff run --bracket config/playoff_2026.toml
52	
53	# Or without installation
54	python -m worldcup_playoff run --bracket config/playoff_2026.toml
55	```
56	
57	## CLI Reference
58	
59	All commands accept `--verbose` / `-v` (countable: `-v` for INFO, `-vv` for DEBUG). Most accept `--config` / `-c` (default: `config/default.toml`).
60	
61	### Data Acquisition
62	
63	#### `download`
64	
65	Bulk-download all World Cup datasets from football-data.org in one pass (`teams.csv`, `matches.csv`, `ranking.csv`, `players.csv`, `match_details.csv`).
66	
67	```bash
68	worldcup-playoff download --seasons 2006-2026 --output-dir dataset/csv
69	worldcup-playoff download --only matches,teams --seasons 2018-2026
70	worldcup-playoff download --skip-details  # skip match_details.csv
71	```
72	
73	| Flag | Default | Description |
74	|------|---------|-------------|
75	| `--seasons` | `2006-2026` | Season range as `START-END` (4-digit years) |
76	| `--output-dir` | `dataset/csv` | Output directory for all CSVs |
77	| `--skip-details` | `False` | Skip `match_details.csv` |
78	| `--only` | all | Comma-separated subset: `teams`, `matches`, `ranking`, `players`, `match-details` |
79	
80	#### `build-teams`
81	
82	Fetch national-team metadata across major competitions (`WC`, `EC`, `CA`) and write `teams.csv`.
83	
84	```bash
85	worldcup-playoff build-teams --output-dir dataset/csv
86	```
87	
88	| Flag | Default | Description |
89	|------|---------|-------------|
90	| `--output-dir` | `dataset/csv` | Output directory for `teams.csv` |
91	
92	#### `build-matches`
93	
94	Fetch finished match results per competition per season and assemble `matches.csv`.
95	
96	```bash
97	worldcup-playoff build-matches --start-year 2006 --end-year 2026
98	```
99	
100	| Flag | Default | Description |
101	|------|---------|-------------|
102	| `--start-year` | `2006` | First season year to query |
103	| `--end-year` | current year | Last season year to query |
104	| `--output-dir` | `dataset/csv` | Output directory for `matches.csv` |
105	
106	#### `build-match-details`
107	
108	Fetch per-match detail statistics for every match ID in `matches.csv` and assemble `match_details.csv`. Supports checkpointing (a `.partial` file) so an interrupted run resumes without re-fetching.
109	
110	```bash
111	worldcup-playoff build-match-details --matches-csv dataset/csv/matches.csv
112	```
113	
114	| Flag | Default | Description |
115	|------|---------|-------------|
116	| `--matches-csv` | `dataset/csv/matches.csv` | Source CSV to pull match IDs from |
117	| `--checkpoint-every` | `100` | Save partial progress every N matches |
118	| `--output-dir` | `dataset/csv` | Output directory for `match_details.csv` |
119	
120	> **Note on heuristics:** the free tier does not expose shots, possession, or pass accuracy per match. When those fields are absent the builder fills them with **fixed, deterministic** formulae (never random): `SHOTS = goals * 5 + 7`, `SHOTS_ON_TARGET = max(goals + 2, shots // 3)`, `POSSESSION = 50.0`, `PASS_PCT = 75.0`. A paid tier exposing `TOTAL_SHOTS` / `SHOTS_ON_TARGET` / `BALL_POSSESSION` / `PASS_ACCURACY` statistics overrides the heuristics automatically.
121	
122	#### `generate-bracket`
123	
124	Auto-generate a knockout bracket TOML from the competition's qualified teams (Round of 32, seed `1 vs 32`, `2 vs 31`, …).
125	
126	```bash
127	worldcup-playoff generate-bracket --season 2026
128	worldcup-playoff generate-bracket --output config/playoff_2026.toml
129	```
130	
131	| Flag | Default | Description |
132	|------|---------|-------------|
133	| `--season` / `-s` | auto-detected | World Cup year (e.g. `2026`) |
134	| `--competition` | `WC` | football-data.org competition code |
135	| `--output` / `-o` | `config/playoff_{year}.toml` | Output TOML path |
136	
137	### Pipeline Stages
138	
139	#### `clean`
140	
141	Stage 1: Read raw CSVs, merge `matches.csv` with `match_details.csv` on `MATCH_ID`, filter by `min_date`, drop drawn matches, fix zero possession/pass-pct values with epsilon, add the binary `HOME_WIN` target, and write `dataset/train_data.csv`.
142	
143	```bash
144	worldcup-playoff clean
145	```
146	
147	#### `train`
148	
149	Stage 2: Train one or more classifiers (temporal split), print evaluation metrics, save models.
150	
151	```bash
152	worldcup-playoff train --classifier all          # svm, random-forest, naive-bayes, or all
153	```
154	
155	| Flag | Default | Description |
156	|------|---------|-------------|
157	| `--classifier` | `all` | `svm`, `random-forest`, `naive-bayes`, or `all` |
158	
159	#### `fit`
160	
161	Stage 3: Fit scipy statistical distributions to each national team's per-feature performance data.
162	
163	```bash
164	worldcup-playoff fit
165	```
166	
167	#### `simulate`
168	
169	Stage 4: Run the Monte Carlo knockout simulation (requires pre-trained models and distributions).
170	
171	```bash
172	worldcup-playoff simulate --bracket config/playoff_2026.toml --n-simulations 10000
173	```
174	
175	| Flag | Default | Description |
176	|------|---------|-------------|
177	| `--bracket` / `-b` | `config/playoff_2026.toml` | Bracket TOML file |
178	| `--n-simulations` / `-n` | from config (10000) | Override simulation count |
179	
180	#### `bracket`
181	
182	Simulate and render a bracket PNG visualization.
183	
184	```bash
185	worldcup-playoff bracket --bracket config/playoff_2026.toml --output output/plots/bracket.png
186	```
187	
188	| Flag | Default | Description |
189	|------|---------|-------------|
190	| `--bracket` / `-b` | `config/playoff_2026.toml` | Bracket TOML file |
191	| `--n-simulations` / `-n` | from config | Override simulation count |
192	| `--output` / `-o` | `output/plots/bracket.png` | Output PNG path |
193	
194	#### `run`
195	
196	Execute the full pipeline end-to-end: clean, train all classifiers, fit distributions, simulate, and save visualizations.
197	
198	```bash
199	worldcup-playoff run --bracket config/playoff_2026.toml
200	```
201	
202	| Flag | Default | Description |
203	|------|---------|-------------|
204	| `--bracket` / `-b` | `config/playoff_2026.toml` | Bracket TOML file |
